National Meeting Held to Mark Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Assumption of Supreme Commandership of KPA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the April 25 House of Culture Saturday to mark the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army.
 Present there were senior party, army and state officials, chairpersons of the friendly parties and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA Vice-Marshal Kim Yong Chun, member of the DPRK National Defence Commission and chief of the KPA General Staff, made a report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the revolutionary armed forces 15 years ago marked a great auspicious event of the nation as it provided a sure guarantee for carving out the destiny of our party, the homeland and the people and an epoch-making event that opened a bright prospect of winning sure victory in the Korean revolution and the building of revolutionary armed forces despite grim tempest of history, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since he began his Songun revolutionary leadership early in the 1960s Kim Jong Il has wisely led the cause of army building, having a firm grip on the WPK's idea of attaching importance to the army and the military affairs, thus bringing about a historic turn in building Juche-oriented revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With deep insight into the new situation the Korean revolution faced at home and abroad due to the imperialist reactionary forces' frantic anti-socialist offensive, he established the Songun politics as a major socialist political mode in all fields and successfully solved the issue of forming a main force of the revolution on the principle of placing the army ahead of the working class as required by the era and the developing revolution, thereby putting the Songun revolutionary cause of Juche on a new higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the situation where the U.S. imperialists have become ever more undisguised in their threat of a preemptive nuclear attack and sanctions and pressure, the army and people of the DPRK have made utmost efforts to bolster the national defence capacity to defend the sovereignty and the right to existence of the country and the nation and thanks to this persevering struggle the DPRK succeeded in developing nukes and emerged a full-fledged nuclear weapons state after going through the most just and fair processes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its successful nuclear test was a historic event that strikingly demonstrated the strong power and creative potential of Juche Korea advancing under the great banner of Songun. It was a shining fruition of the unshakable faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to unfailingly achieve the ideal of independence and prosperity without allowing their national dignity and destiny to be infringed upon by any other country in the world plagued with tragic events due to the prevalence of the law of jungle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the tasks facing the army and people, the reporter underscored the need to defend Kim Jong Il politico-ideologically and at the cost of their lives in any adversity, thoroughly establish the trait of attaching importance to the army in the whole society and continue channeling primary efforts into developing the national defence industry, the material foundation of the military capacity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called for exerting increased state efforts for the socialist economic construction to revitalize national economy and improve the standard of the people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reiterating that it is the sacred duty the Korean people assumed before the times and history to end the tragic national division and reunify the country, the reporter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation on the Korean Peninsula still remains unpredictable due to the U.S. unchanged hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has blocked the implementation of the September 19 joint statement and put the six-party talks to a deadlock for more than a year by applying unreasonable sanctions against the DPRK. At the resumed talks it persistently schemed to force the DPRK to disarm itself unilaterally while categorically rejecting the prompt lift of the sanctions and insisting that the DPRK abandon its nuclear program first &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and its followers including Japan have persistently kicked up anti-DPRK "human rights" racket and tightened sanctions against it in a reckless bid to impair the dignity and prestige of the DPRK and strangle it economically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is closely watching with a high degree of vigilance the U.S. busy employing all sorts of tricks to wrest unilateral concession and disarmament from the DPRK, using carrot and stick and escalating sanctions under the signboard of "dialogue."  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sanctions and pressure will never work on the DPRK. If the hostile forces continue escalating sanctions and pressure against the DPRK, it will resolutely react to them with stronger countermeasures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK want peace but they are not afraid of war. They will never allow anyone to infringe upon the sovereignty and dignity of their country even a bit.

Homage to Kim Jong Suk Paid 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 24 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the bust of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on Sunday on the occasion of her 89th birth anniversary.
 Seen before the bust was a wreath from General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying event were senior party, army and state officials, chairpersons of the friendly parties, members of the Cabinet, officials of party, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and servicepersons, working people from all social standings and school youth and children in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the wreath-laying music, wreaths were laid before the bust in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed were wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, KPA units and educational, health and press organs, the organizations of the Korean Children's Union, and party and power bodies, factories and farms in the city and bouquets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of those wreaths were letters "The revolutionary exploits of anti-Japanese war hero Comrade Kim Jong Suk are immortal!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, floral baskets were placed before the statues of Kim Jong Suk in Kim Jong Suk County and Hoeryong City and at Kim Jong Suk Naval Academy and Kim Jong Suk General Military Academy that day.

DPRK to Closely Watch U.S. Attitude 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, December 22 (KCNA Correspondent) -- The Democratic People's Republic of Korea will closely watch the U.S. future attitude, declared Kim Kye Gwan, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs who headed the DPRK delegation to the six-party talks, when interviewed by mediapersons in Beijing on Friday.
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We clarified our will to realize denuclearization at the talks and participated in them despite sanctions. We, therefore, urged the U.S. to lift sanctions against the DPRK, to begin with, and start the discussion on the issue of denuclearization. The U.S., however, demanded a stop to our nuclear activities and verification of them without taking any action for lifting the sanctions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We decisively opposed this and told the U.S. side to further study our proposal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the chairman's statement was adopted at the six-party talks.

DPRK's Important Days Marked in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 24 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held in Moscow on Dec. 20 under the sponsorship of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK to mark the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 Speakers at the meeting said that the Korean people have rosy future as they are led by Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole life of Kim Jong Suk was a noble life devoted to the country, the people and the revolutionary comrades, they said, adding that her august name will be enshrined in the mind of the progressive humankind forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Seminars, meetings, film shows and book, photo and handicraft exhibitions were held between Dec. 12 and 16 by the Centre for the Study of the Juche Idea of Mongolian Chinggis Khan College and in Bern and Sofia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, photos showing their immortal exploits and books, photos and handiworks introducing the achievements made by the Korean people in building socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean films including "The Rivers and Mountains of the Country Being Face-lifted under the Leadership of the Great General," "The Fatherly Leader among Anti-Japanese Revolutionary Fighters" and "The Great Leader Steering the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation to Victory" were shown at film shows. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory messages to Kim Jong Il were adopted at meetings in Russia and Switzerland.

Art Performance Given by KPA Song and Dance Ensemble 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 24 (KCNA) -- A music and dance performance "Glory to the General" was given by the Korean People's Army Song and Dance Ensemble at the April 25 House of Culture on Dec. 23 to celebrate the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the KPA supreme commandership.
 It was appreciated by senior party, army and state officials, chairpersons of the friendly parties, Cabinet members, officials of party, armed forces and power organs, social organizations, ministries and national institutions and servicepersons and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance, which began with mixed chorus "Glory to the General," truthfully represented the high honor and pride of the Korean nation in having Kim Jong Il at the top post of the revolutionary armed forces and the revolutionary zeal and militant spirit of the Korean army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its numbers included piano duet and mixed chorus "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il," male vocal solo "The Leader Visits Military Post," female folk duet "We Sing of Our Country Holding Leader in High Esteem" and dance "A Recruit Arrives." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers highly lauded the undying feats of Kim Jong Il who opened the bright vista of building a great prosperous powerful nation with his original Songun policy while commanding the revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance ended with mixed chorus "Let's Support Our Supreme Commander with Arms." It was acclaimed by the audience for its high ideological and artistic value.

Servicepersons' Evening Gala Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 24 (KCNA) -- An evening gala of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces took place at Jonsung Plaza on Dec. 23 to celebrate the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army.
 Seen on the platform there were Vice Marshal of the KPA Jo Myong Rok, director of the KPA General Political Department, Vice Marshal of the KPA Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, and leading officials of the ministry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of "Song of General Kim Jong Il" the participants in the gala unrolled a wave of dances with deep reverence of the army and people for Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Servicepersons delightfully danced to the tune of "Soldiers Present Glory," "Our General Is Best," "Let's Sing of Our Pride in Being under the Guidance of the General" and other songs, with their high honor and pride of being blessed with illustrious leaders and generals generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The evening gala went on with songs "Twelve Months for Songun Victory," "Military Service in Company Is Delightful," "Let's Keep Pace to the Tune of Army Song" and "Arirang for Prosperity," which vividly represent the great pride of soldiers being under the command of Kim Jong Il and optimism of the Songun victors demonstrating their high mettle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Merrily dancing to the tune of songs "Thunder on Jong Il Peak," "General on a Galloping White Horse," "All Servicepersons and People Will Become Human Bullets and Bombs," "We Will Defend the Headquarters of Revolution with Our Lives" and other songs, all the participants renewed their firm determination to reliably guarantee the cause of the Worker's Party of Korea with arms under the guidance of Kim Jong Il.

Papers Observe Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Assumption of KPA Supreme Commandership 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 24 (KCNA) -- Today marks the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army.
 Newspapers here today dedicate editorials to the anniversary stressing that his assumption was a historic event which brought about an epochal turn in strengthening the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK and achieving prosperity of socialist Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 15 years when Kim Jong Il led the Korean revolution and the socialist cause after assuming the important office as KPA supreme commander is the sacred annals that recorded immortal traces in the history of the country and the nation, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He secured powerful military deterrent after putting the military affairs above other state affairs and thus raised the dignity and position of the country and the nation to the highest level. This is the especially noteworthy exploit in the history of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The country liberated by President Kim Il Sung with arms is now shining as a socialist power under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has placed the single-minded unity of our revolutionary ranks with the KPA as its core and mainstay on a higher stage. This is the great exploit as it brought rosy future for victory of the socialist cause. The single-minded unity now serves as an emblem of Songun Korea and the source of all victories of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He encouraged the army and people to usher in a new era of building a great prosperous powerful nation, a new history of great changes. This exploit will remain forever in the history of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation the Korean army and people are faced with heavy yet honorable tasks to open up a new heyday of national prosperity under the great banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the servicepersons and people should dynamically advance along the road of Songun revolution, bearing deep in mind high national pride and honor of being led by Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should trust in and follow only Kim Jong Il in any adversity with rock-firm faith that he represents their destiny and future and their country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should consistently glorify the proud history and tradition of the Songun revolution in which they have devotedly defended the respected supreme commander, acting as fortress and shield. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to thoroughly apply the Songun politics and the line of Songun revolution of the Workers' Party of Korea and further increase the country's self-defensive military capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All of them should be ardent adherents to the Songun idea and resolute defender and implementer of the idea and push forward all the work including the building of the party, state and armed forces through the political mode of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should display ardent patriotic enthusiasm so as to make a new leap in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson stresses that the victory of the Songun revolution is in store as long as Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu, stands in the van of the Korean revolutionary armed forces and the army and people are closely united around him as one in mind.

Kim Jong Il Lauded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 24 (KCNA) -- The vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front (AINDF) issued a statement on Dec. 23 on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army and the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk, according to the Internet site Kuguk Jonson.
 He said that the history and tradition of the revolutionary cause of Juche President Kim Il Sung started and led to victory with arms are creditably being carried forward and a sure guarantee for its accomplishment was provided with Kim Jong Il standing at the head of the revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spirit of national reconciliation, unity and reunification is prevalent and the anti-American struggle is growing stronger in this land as the days go by. The credit for this goes to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il who provided the historic June 15 joint declaration with the matchless Songun policy and the national reunification line and policies based on this to open the epoch-making phase of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The self-defensive war deterrent of the north, a product of Songun, is very instrumental in helping the Korean people attain a decisive victory in the stand-off with the U.S. and achieve peace and reunification of Korea. It is the greatest pride and privilege for all the Koreans to have Kim Jong Il as supreme commander of the KPA, who ushered in the era of the most brilliant victory and glory in the five thousand-year history of the nation by pursuing the great Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vanguard fighters of the AINDF and the patriotic people from all walks of life will more positively support and defend the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il, following Kim Jong Suk who set the noble example of loyalty to the President in life and struggle, and remain true to the leadership of Kim Jong Il for the national reunification in one mind and purpose.

Important Day of DPRK Celebrated in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks, film shows and photo exhibitions took place in the Czech Republic, Russia, India and Indonesia between Dec. 14 and 18 to mark the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army.
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were photos showing the immortal feats performed by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, the might of the heroic KPA and the achievements made by the Korean people in building socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film shows watched "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Provides On-site Guidance to Different Sectors", "The Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks" and other Korean films. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first secretary of the Czechoslovak Communist Party in a round-table talk noted that the heroic struggle of the Korean people reliably defending socialism from the moves of the U.S., styling itself the "only superpower" in the world has given encouragement to the world progressive people desirous of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general manager of the Interoptsik Company of Russia said after watching the Korean film that all the miraculous events taking place in the DPRK are unthinkable without the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the Indian Institute for the Foreign Policy said at the end of the film show that the reality of the DPRK proves that even a small country can work miracles of history if it has the leader with rare wisdom, distinguished leadership ability and matchless courage and pluck.

Japanese Militarists' Criminal Acts under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The reactionaries of the land of Japs have frantically incited militarism in the Japanese society since they set it as their general goal for this year to completely scrap the "pacifist constitution" and adopt instead a new war constitution and revise the "Law on Self-Defence Forces (SDF)" in a bid to secure a legal mechanism for realizing their wild ambition for overseas aggression. 
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The political development in Japan this year goes to prove that the desperate moves of the Japanese militarist forces to realize their ambition for overseas expansion at any cost have assumed more dangerous nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The militarist propaganda offensive has become evermore pronounced in the Japanese society this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries more frequently visited the "Yasukuni Shrine" defying strong rebuff and criticism at home and abroad. Lurking behind this was a sinister intention to implant in the minds of the Japanese, school youth and children, in particular, pride of the Japanese imperialists' history of aggression, the spirit of exacting revenge for their defeat and the wild ambition to realize their domination over Asia which they failed to do so in the past and thus lay an ideological and moral foundation for attaining their militarist goal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year the Japanese reactionaries have busied themselves with the moves to create legal conditions for successful advance of the SDF overseas and its overseas military operations and increase its combat capability, while steadily tightening the military nexus between Japan and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that they have boosted their collusion and tie-up with the U.S. imperialists in the moves to establish the missile defence system (MD). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said moves this year are characterized by the fact that they have shifted to buckling down to establishing in real earnest the Japan-U.S. joint missile defence system with Japan as a base from escalating their nexus with the U.S. in the field of missile defence, avoiding the attention of the international community under the signboard of "joint research." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The moves of the Japanese reactionaries to establish the MD presuppose a preemptive missile attack on other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year they have relaxed the "three principles of arms export" and bolstered the SDF in an effort to increase its capability for overseas military operations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their attempt to soften the "three principles of arms export" was prompted by their wicked intention to get rid of one more brake on their moves to turn Japan into a military power and realize the nuclear weaponization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have also worked hard to boost the SDF's capability for preemptive attack this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director general of the Defense Agency and other high-ranking military and political officials of Japan did not bother to bluster that Japan should be capable of mounting preemptive attacks on other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently the Japanese Diet finally adopted the law on upgrading the Defense Agency to the ministry. This is a very dangerous legal action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is noteworthy in the militarist moves of the Japanese reactionaries this year is that they have stepped up the moves to cook up a war constitution to replace the "pacifist constitution" which has existed for decades in Japan in name only. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries singled out the DPRK as the primary target of their overseas aggression. Accordingly, they have become evermore frantic in their moves to stage a comeback to Korea this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First of all, they have made desperate efforts to impair the international prestige of the dignified DPRK. The ultra-right conservative forces of the land of Japs have made much fuss, publishing and distributing even pamphlets on the "abduction issue." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities have conducted such disgusting diplomacy as inviting panjandrums of other countries to their country to join in their anti-DPRK campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries have been hell bent on the "sanctions" against the DPRK and the moves for "preemptive attack" on it this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Toeing its American master's policy, the Japanese government decided to apply "financial sanctions" against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's sanctions against the DPRK have reached an extreme phase as evidenced by total embargo on its ships including Mangyongbong-92. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reactionaries of the island country have justified their moves to convert it into a military power and the moves for reinvasion with a hue and cry over the "threat" from the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The criminal nature and gravity of Japan's hostile policy toward the DPRK have found a striking manifestation in its brutal suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), a legitimate organization of overseas citizens of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole land of Japan has been swept by a whirlwind of unprecedented crackdown upon Chongryon and Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As seen above, the Japanese reactionaries' moves for militarization and overseas aggression assumed more grave and dangerous nature this year than any other years.

Functions Held by Youth and Students and Women
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held by youth and students at the Central Youth Hall on Dec. 22 in celebration of the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army.
 The reporter and speakers at the meeting noted that illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the KPA meant great fortune for the servicepersons and young and other people of the DPRK as they are blessed with the general and full of pride and dignity of living in Kim Il Sung's Korea, adding that this marked a great historic event of epochal significance in developing the Korean revolution and accomplishing the Juche-oriented cause of army building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They referred to the fact that Kim Jong Il put forward the youth as a detached force and a reserve combat unit of the supreme commander and led them with profound loving care to demonstrate the honor of being front rankers in the Songun revolution which perform heroic feats in defending the country and building a prosperous nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the young people to prepare themselves as Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary comrades who share will and destiny with him any time and in any place and indomitable vanguard fighters devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution, enshrining faith in certain victory that they are sure to emerge victorious if they are led by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the C.C., the WPK was present there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day a performance was given by an art squad of the C.C., the youth league and a performance "Our country is great as it is led by the illustrious Songun commander of Mt. Paektu" by members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union in celebration of the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the KPA and the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.

New Documentary Film Screened
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- Part 23 of documentary "Under the Guidance of the Great Brilliant Commander" was screened at the People's Palace of Culture Friday on the occasion of the 15th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army.
 The film was watched by senior party and state officials, Cabinet members, officials of working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film edits historic data showing that Kim Jong Il tirelessly provided energetic guidance to develop the People's Army into an army intensely loyal to the party and the leader and devoted to the country and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It tells how wisely Kim Jong Il led the servicepersons to devotedly help people in terms of politico-ideology and manpower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It deals with the struggle of servicepersons performing labor feats in key domains of the national economy. True to the high intention of the supreme commander, the servicepersons built power stations, factories and enterprises and other edifices of Songun era in different parts of the country and took the lead in aiding the agricultural front, key front of economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film tells that as there is loving care shown by the great Songun brilliant commander there produced a number of moving stories that soldiers devote their own lives without hesitation to defend the lives and property of the people.

Sinpha Revolutionary Site Attracts Endless Stream of Visitors
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hyesan, December 22 (KCNA) -- An endless stream of servicepersons, people from all walks of life and school youth and children are visiting the Sinpha revolutionary site on the occasion of the 89th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 The number of visitors to the site reached more than 138,000 this year alone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is the historical place where Kim Jong Suk conducted revolutionary activities after being assigned an underground political work by President Kim Il Sung during the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors placed floral baskets, bouquets and flowers before her statue standing in the revolutionary site before paying tribute to her in humble reverence. They went round different places in the site.

Kim Jong Suk's Efforts on Making Military Colors
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The people in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, with deep reverence, are looking back on the immortal feats performed by anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk in making the military colors on the occasion of her birth anniversary which falls on December 24.
 On an autumn day in Juche 36 (1947), she attended the graduation ceremony of the Central Security Officers School and was very excited with boundless joy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  After coming back from the function, she sat at her desk and was engrossed in drawing something on a blank paper. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A few officials quietly entered the room, fearing lest they would interrupt her thinking. One of them asked her what she was drawing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking in their faces, she said with bright smile that there would be a military parade with military colors in the van of units and so she was designing the military colors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several days later, she showed some designs of military colors to President Kim Il Sung and discussed them with him all the night. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the designs were decided, she frequented the workshop making military colors and personally embroidered them with sincerity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then she earnestly told that the Korean army, in future, would become an army strongest in the world and demonstrate its invincible might forever to the world as the ever-victorious revolutionary armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indeed, the Korean People�fs Army is displaying its invincible might all over the world as she wished, frustrating all sorts of vicious provocations of the enemies.

Suppression of Chongryon in Japan under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The chairman of the Group for the Study of the Progressive Idea of the North Pretoria Branch of the South African Democratic Teachers' Union in a statement on Dec. 16 condemned the Japanese reactionaries for their unreasonable crackdown on the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon).
 He stressed that Chongryon is a full-fledged overseas citizens organization of the DPRK which has the deserved rights to be protected by Japan's law and the international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities' suppression aimed at schools and students under Chongryon is the most barbarous deed that can be justified and defended with nothing, the statement said. And it strongly urged the Japanese authorities to halt the crackdown upon Chongryon, the educational institutions and students in particular, at once and unconditionally compensate for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon the UN and the world human rights bodies and media to pay due attention to the Japanese authorities' suppression of Chongryon and put such behavior on the top agenda of international conferences on human rights issues and take relevant legal action against it.
